For production environments with dynamic origins, you need a centralized CORS middleware with proper validation, caching, and monitoring. Never blindly reflect the Origin header - always validate against a trusted source.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
// src/Middleware/CorsMiddleware.php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Middleware;

use App\Services\OriginValidator;
use App\Services\AuditLogger;
use Psr\Http\Message\ResponseInterface;
use Psr\Http\Message\ServerRequestInterface;
use Psr\Http\Server\MiddlewareInterface;
use Psr\Http\Server\RequestHandlerInterface;

class CorsMiddleware implements MiddlewareInterface
{
    private OriginValidator $originValidator;
    private AuditLogger $logger;
    private array $config;

    public function __construct(
        OriginValidator $originValidator,
        AuditLogger $logger,
        array $config
    ) {
        $this->originValidator = $originValidator;
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->config = $config;
    }

    public function process(
        ServerRequestInterface $request,
        RequestHandlerInterface $handler
    ): ResponseInterface {
        $origin = $request->getHeaderLine('Origin');

        // Handle preflight
        if ($request->getMethod() === 'OPTIONS') {
            return $this->handlePreflight($request, $origin);
        }

        $response = $handler->handle($request);
        return $this->addCorsHeaders($response, $origin, $request);
    }

    private function handlePreflight(
        ServerRequestInterface $request,
        string $origin
    ): ResponseInterface {
        $response = new \Nyholm\Psr7\Response(204);

        if (!$this->isOriginAllowed($origin)) {
            $this->logger->warning('CORS preflight rejected', [
                'origin' => $origin,
                'ip' => $request->getServerParams()['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown',
                'user_agent' => $request->getHeaderLine('User-Agent')
            ]);
            return $response; // No CORS headers = browser blocks request
        }

        return $this->addCorsHeaders($response, $origin, $request);
    }

    private function addCorsHeaders(
        ResponseInterface $response,
        string $origin,
        ServerRequestInterface $request
    ): ResponseInterface {
        if (!$this->isOriginAllowed($origin)) {
            return $response;
        }

        $response = $response
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', $origin)
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials', 'true')
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', implode(', ', $this->config['allowed_methods']))
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', implode(', ', $this->config['allowed_headers']))
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Expose-Headers', implode(', ', $this->config['expose_headers']))
            ->withHeader('Access-Control-Max-Age', (string)$this->config['max_age'])
            ->withHeader('Vary', 'Origin');

        // Log successful CORS request for monitoring
        $this->logger->info('CORS request allowed', [
            'origin' => $origin,
            'method' => $request->getMethod(),
            'path' => $request->getUri()->getPath()
        ]);

        return $response;
    }

    private function isOriginAllowed(string $origin): bool {
        if (empty($origin)) {
            return false;
        }

        // Validate URL format first
        if (!filter_var($origin, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL)) {
            return false;
        }

        $parsedOrigin = parse_url($origin);
        if (!$parsedOrigin || !isset($parsedOrigin['host'])) {
            return false;
        }

        // Check against validator (handles static list, DB, and subdomain patterns)
        return $this->originValidator->isAllowed($origin);
    }
}

// src/Services/OriginValidator.php
class OriginValidator
{
    private \PDO $pdo;
    private \Psr\SimpleCache\CacheInterface $cache;
    private array $staticOrigins;
    private array $subdomainPatterns;

    public function __construct(
        \PDO $pdo,
        \Psr\SimpleCache\CacheInterface $cache,
        array $config
    ) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
        $this->cache = $cache;
        $this->staticOrigins = $config['static_origins'] ?? [];
        $this->subdomainPatterns = $config['subdomain_patterns'] ?? [];
    }

    public function isAllowed(string $origin): bool {
        // Check static whitelist first (fastest)
        if (in_array($origin, $this->staticOrigins, true)) {
            return true;
        }

        // Check subdomain patterns (e.g., *.myapp.com)
        if ($this->matchesSubdomainPattern($origin)) {
            return true;
        }

        // Check database with caching
        return $this->checkDatabaseOrigin($origin);
    }

    private function matchesSubdomainPattern(string $origin): bool {
        $parsedOrigin = parse_url($origin);
        if (!isset($parsedOrigin['host'])) {
            return false;
        }

        $host = $parsedOrigin['host'];
        $scheme = $parsedOrigin['scheme'] ?? 'https';

        // Only allow HTTPS in production
        if ($_ENV['APP_ENV'] === 'production' && $scheme !== 'https') {
            return false;
        }

        foreach ($this->subdomainPatterns as $pattern) {
            // Pattern format: '*.myapp.com'
            $regex = '/^' . str_replace('\*', '[a-zA-Z0-9-]+', preg_quote($pattern, '/')) . '$/';
            if (preg_match($regex, $host)) {
                // Additional validation: no double dots, reasonable length
                if (strpos($host, '..') === false && strlen($host) <= 253) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }

    private function checkDatabaseOrigin(string $origin): bool {
        $cacheKey = 'cors_origin_' . hash('sha256', $origin);

        // Check cache first
        if ($this->cache->has($cacheKey)) {
            return $this->cache->get($cacheKey);
        }

        // Query database
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare(
            'SELECT 1 FROM allowed_origins 
             WHERE origin = :origin 
             AND is_active = 1 
             AND (expires_at IS NULL OR expires_at > NOW())'
        );
        $stmt->execute(['origin' => $origin]);
        $allowed = (bool)$stmt->fetch();

        // Cache for 5 minutes
        $this->cache->set($cacheKey, $allowed, 300);

        return $allowed;
    }
}

// config/cors.php - Production configuration
return [
    'static_origins' => [
        'https://myapp.com',
        'https://www.myapp.com',
        'https://admin.myapp.com',
    ],
    'subdomain_patterns' => [
        '*.myapp.com',           // Customer subdomains
        '*.staging.myapp.com',   // Staging environments
    ],
    'allowed_methods' => ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'PATCH', 'DELETE', 'OPTIONS'],
    'allowed_headers' => [
        'Accept',
        'Authorization',
        'Content-Type',
        'X-Requested-With',
        'X-CSRF-Token',
    ],
    'expose_headers' => [
        'X-Request-Id',
        'X-RateLimit-Remaining',
    ],
    'max_age' => 3600,
];
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Input Validation**: Origin URL must be valid format before any checking
